news.title: Construction and demolition waste plant to be inaugurated soon in Ludhiana
news.para: The construction and demolition (C&D) waste plant set up in Dhandhari was initially conceived under the Smart City Mission but was taken up under the Swachh Bharat Mission due to increase in its cost and change in the structure.

news.title: Over 150 unsafe buildings identified in Ludhiana
news.para: According to the fresh survey, zone D has the maximum number of unsafe buildings, which is 55, whereas zone A, which comprises the old city, has 48 unsafe buildings. Zone B and zone C have 21 and 35 unsafe buildings, respectively.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body frees ₹800 crore land for Indirapuram Extension project
news.para: A GDA official said the land parcel will be clubbed with the Indirapuram Extension scheme — covering an area of 34 hectares — where the development authority is planning a new township.

news.title: No homes on zudpi jungles will be demolished: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Chairing a high-level meeting at Mantralaya to address the long standing issue, Bawankule warned senior officials from revenue and forest departments that delays in regularising such homes will not be tolerated.

news.title: Noida authority urges Uttar Pradesh government to review Gardenia Aims Developers' debt plan
news.para: The authority said that if allowed, the move would contradict a cabinet-approved policy for stalled projects, which requires defaulting builders to deposit 25% of dues before accessing relief measures.

news.title: Consumer forum fines GEAPL & Shriram Properties for eight-year flat delay in Vizag
news.para: The commission further directed Global Entropolis Asia Pvt Ltd (GEAPL) and Shriram Properties Pvt Ltd to register and deliver the fully furnished 2,011 sq ft flat to the complainant.

news.title: Delhi civic body extends 10% property tax rebate till July 31
news.para: The meeting was chaired by Satya Sharma, the newly appointed Chairperson of the Standing Committee, and saw active participation from all members, who discussed a wide range of issues concerning public welfare.

news.title: Prestige & Arihant Group to jointly acquire land in Chennai for ₹361.18 crore
news.para: The land is earmarked for the development of residential dwellings with a total development potential of approximately 7.5 lakh sq ft and an estimated gross development value (GDV) of over ₹1,600 crore.​​

news.title: Miami's Brickell City Centre sold to Simon Property in up to $548.7 million deal
news.para: Brickell City Centre stretches across four floors and features more than 90 retail stores, anchored by Saks Fifth Avenue. It forms part of a mixed-use development in Miami's financial district, which also includes office and residential towers as well as a hotel.

news.title: Women’s participation can play key role in beautification of India's Smart Cities: Minister
news.para: D Thara, additional secretary, Union Ministry of Housing & Urban Affairs emphasized on the need for looking beyond developing the buildings and housing complexes and aim for integrated infrastructure management in order to achieve a sustainable habitat.

news.title: NTT has lodged preliminary prospectus to list REIT on Singapore Exchange
news.para: The prospectus did not disclose the IPO amount but the two sources had said in January it could be worth up to $1 billion in what would be the largest in Singapore in several years. The prospectus also did not say when the IPO would be launched.

news.title: Rampant constructions near Pune airport may put funnel zone at risk: Experts
news.para: Referring to the Pune Municipal Corporation's action this week against illegal under-construction buildings in the vicinity of the airport, the experts said too little was being done too late. An Indian Air Force (IAF) veteran, requesting anonymity, said rampant construction around airports couldn't have happened without collusion.

news.title: Wakefit Innovations files draft papers with Sebi; seeks to raise ₹468 crore via fresh issue
news.para: The proposed IPO of the Bengaluru-based company is a combination of a fresh issue of equity shares aggregating up to Rs 468.2 crore and an offer for sale (OFS) of 5.84 crore equity shares by the selling shareholders, according to the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) filed on Thursday.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to spend ₹10.25 crore on basic services for Manimajra land parcel
news.para: Of this, Rs 4.96 crore has been allocated for public health services, Rs 3.32 crore for road works, Rs 99 lakh for horticulture, and Rs 37 lakh for electrical works. Also, Rs 30 lakh has been set aside for a common duct to carry networking lines for multiple services.

news.title: Sobha to invest ₹800 crore in residential project in Greater Noida
news.para: The project spread over 3.46 acres and have a total development potential of approximately 9.3 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Randeep Hooda buys an apartment worth ₹5.63 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Randeep Hooda's apartment has a built-up area of 142.19 sq meter (1,530 sq ft). The transaction was registered in June 2025.

news.title: Probe ordered into alleged TDR scam on reserved land in Deolali
news.para: Ram Shinde, the state legislative council chairman, said the complaint indicates NMC issued TDR certificates to the landowner concerned at a rate of Rs 25,100 per sqmt, while govt market value of the reserved land at Deolali was Rs 6,500 per sqmt.

news.title: Slums in Bhopal's central area to shift
news.para: Information suggests that nine slum settlements situated near Vallabh Bhawan will be shifted to Banganga, near Jinsi and other locations where estimated 14,000 permanent residences will be built through a Public-Private Partnership (PPP) arrangement.

news.title: Delay in tax recovery from merged areas hampers Pune civic body's revenue generation
news.para: The state govt has put a cap on charging "maximum of twice the property tax compared to what the residents were paying when they were under gram panchayat" but the nitty-gritty of the implementation has not been worked out by the state govt, claimed PMC.

news.title: Structural study of Margao’s unsafe buildings finally begins
news.para: Acting on direct orders from South Goa collector Egna Cleetus, a team from Goa College of Engineering (GEC) conducted inspections of four buildings earlier this week.
